cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in super-resolution (SR) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel recursive unit that involves channel attention and multi-level feature fusion, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper deals with image processing, it could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
